        keyRules:["Steroid hormones: lipid-soluble → cross membrane → bind intracellular receptor → directly regulate gene expression. Peptide hormones: hydrophilic → bind surface receptor → signal cascade.","Cancer: oncogene = gain-of-function mutation (too much growth signal). Tumor suppressor = loss-of-function (no growth inhibition). Both → uncontrolled division.","G1 checkpoint: p53 detects DNA damage → transcribes p21 → p21 inhibits CDK → cell cycle arrested. Without p53, damaged cells divide.","Meiosis I separates homologs. Meiosis II separates sister chromatids. Result: 4 haploid cells with genetic variation."],
