        keyRules:["Coriolis effect: deflects moving air/water RIGHT in Northern Hemisphere, LEFT in Southern Hemisphere. Causes prevailing wind patterns and ocean gyres.","Soil horizons: O (organic litter) → A (topsoil, most fertile, highest humus) → B (subsoil, mineral accumulation) → C (weathered rock) → R (bedrock).","El Niño: warm Pacific water shifts east → disrupts Walker circulation → droughts in Australia/SE Asia, flooding in Peru/Ecuador.","Thermohaline circulation: cold, salty water sinks in North Atlantic → drives global ocean heat distribution. Climate disruption risk if freshwater input dilutes salinity."],
        resources:[{ name:"Bozeman — Earth Systems", url:"https://www.bozemanscience.com/ap-environmental-science", desc:"Earth systems and resources videos" }],
