        keyRules:["Greenhouse effect: CO₂ and other gases trap outgoing infrared (heat) radiation — natural process. Enhanced greenhouse effect: human emissions amplify trapping → global warming.","CFC catalytic ozone destruction: CFC → UV → Cl radical. Cl + O₃ → ClO + O₂. ClO + O → Cl + O₂. One Cl radical destroys up to 100,000 O₃ molecules.","Photochemical smog: ground-level ozone is a POLLUTANT (different from stratospheric ozone). Formed when NOx and VOCs react with sunlight.","Acid rain: primarily from SO₂ (coal plants, smelters) and NOx (vehicles, power plants). pH < 5.6 damages ecosystems and infrastructure."],
        resources:[{ name:"Bozeman — Climate Change", url:"https://www.bozemanscience.com/ap-environmental-science", desc:"Greenhouse effect, ozone, and air pollution videos" }],
        frq:null,
        tip:"Ozone depletion and climate change are often confused on the exam. Ozone depletion: caused by CFCs, affects stratospheric ozone, increases UV radiation at surface. Climate change: caused by CO₂/CH₄/N₂O, traps heat in troposphere, increases global temperature. Different gases, different mechanisms.",
