        keyRules:["Fiscal policy: Congress and president control (democratic accountability). Monetary policy: Federal Reserve controls (independent, insulated from short-term political pressure).","Entitlement programs (Social Security, Medicare): guaranteed by law to all who qualify; largest portion of federal budget; politically difficult to cut.","Policy implementation: bureaucratic agencies translate laws into actual programs. Congress can influence through oversight hearings, budget control, and confirmation of appointees.","Iron triangle creates policy stability — the same agencies, committees, and interest groups dominate a policy area for years, making major change difficult."],
