        tip:"The preterite vs imperfect distinction is tested in almost every AP Spanish writing task. Simple rule: if the action has a clear beginning and end → preterite. If it's a state, background, or habitual → imperfect. When in doubt, think: 'was this a snapshot (preterite) or a movie playing in the background (imperfect)?'",
