        keyRules:["Formal register: always use 您 when addressing the recipient. Use formal nouns (贵公司, 贵校, 贵单位). Use formal verbs (惠顾 not 光顾, 敬请 not 请).","Address ALL required tasks — AP Chinese email prompts typically have 3-4 specific tasks. Missing any one costs significant points.","Character accuracy: wrong characters (even if phonetically similar) are marked as errors. Proofread especially for 的/地/得 and common homophones.","Email length: aim for at least 80-120 characters of substantive content per task addressed — quality and completeness over brevity."],
