        frq:{ type:"Story Narration", prompt:"Practice with a set of 6 AP Chinese pictures. Write a complete story in 15 minutes (typed). Your story must: connect all 6 pictures with a logical plot, include at least one character's internal thoughts or emotions, and end with a conclusion or lesson learned.", rubricTip:"AP Chinese story rubric: task completion (all 6 pictures addressed, complete story arc), language use (grammar, vocabulary range, character accuracy), delivery (narrative coherence, logical connections). Stories that describe pictures separately without causal connections score in the lower range." },
        tip:"The 6-picture story is unique to AP Chinese (and Japanese). Key strategy: spend the first 30 seconds identifying the setting, main character, and the core problem or event. Then narrate each picture in 2-3 sentences. End with a reflection. This structure reliably earns high scores.",
