        frq:{ type:"FRQ — Rolling Motion", prompt:"A solid sphere (mass M, radius R) starts from rest at the top of an incline (length L, angle θ) and rolls without slipping to the bottom. (a) Draw separate free body diagrams for translation and rotation. (b) Write ΣF = Ma for the translational motion. (c) Write Στ = Iα for the rotational motion about the CM. (d) Use the rolling constraint and I = 2/5 MR² to find the acceleration. (e) Find the speed at the bottom using energy methods.", rubricTip:"Rolling FRQ: earn 1 point for each correctly set-up equation, 1 for correct rolling constraint application, 1 for correct numerical answer for acceleration, 1 for correct energy equation, 1 for correct final speed. Partial credit at every step — never skip to the answer." },
