        frq:{ type:"FRQ — Complete Gauss's Law Problem", prompt:"A coaxial cable has inner conductor (radius a, charge per unit length +λ) and outer cylindrical shell (radius b, charge per unit length -λ). (a) Use Gauss's law to find E for r < a, a < r < b, and r > b. Show all 4 steps for the middle region. (b) Find V(r) for a < r < b by integrating E. (c) Find the capacitance per unit length of this coaxial cable. (d) Find the energy stored per unit length if the cable carries charge per unit length λ.", rubricTip:"Gauss's law FRQ: earn 1 point for choice of Gaussian surface with justification, 1 for setting up the flux integral correctly, 1 for finding Q_enc correctly, 1 for the correct E expression, 1 for the V integral setup, 1 for V(r), 1 for C per unit length, 1 for energy. Partial credit at every step — show all work." },
